Package: convexpi
Title: ConvexPi Lab Client for R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("ConvexPi", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "team@convexpi.ai")
Description: Write quantitative trading strategies in R and submit them to the ConvexPi
    hidden-holdout grader. Provides access to the same synthetic equity market the grader
    uses (via the published Python 'convexpi-lab' through 'reticulate') and a helper to
    submit an R strategy. Strategies are defined as on_day() and scored by the same engine
    as Python and Julia, so the same idea earns the same out-of-sample result in any language.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://www.convexpi.ai
BugReports: https://github.com/convexpi/convexpi-r/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: reticulate, httr, jsonlite
Suggests: websocket, later
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
